rd.";i:18;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:19;s:106:"If the wires appear to be in good shape next look at the control button mounted near your side entry door.";i:20;s:43:"If it is old or dirty the button may stick.";i:21;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:22;s:107:"You press the button to open the garage door and it opens easily enough so you can get your vehicle inside.";i:23;s:124:"Then when you try to close the door with the remote it only goes down a certain amount before it reverses and opens back up.";i:24;s:35:"This is highly frustrating springs.";i:25;s:74:"However it does not usually mean there is a serious problem with the door.";i:26;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:27;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:28;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:29;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:30;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:31;s:15:"Answer 1 of 11.";i:32;s:39:"The most likely culprit is your sensor.";i:33;s:65:"It may be blocked off-track or the settings may be set too short.";i:34;s:78:"Here are the steps I recommend you follow to see if you can fix this yourself.";i:35;s:45:"These are summaries of an article found here.";i:36;s:40:"Your garage door sensor generally has t.";i:37;s:193:"If you release the door from the opener using the release cord see image below you should be able to lift the door to half open by hand and the door should stay at that point if you release it.";i:38;s:40:"If not there is a problem with the door.";i:39;s:100:"There could be a bind or drag in the door mechanism or the springs may be damaged or need adjusting.";i:40;s:85:"Garage Door sometimes opens a few inches and stops then closes and opens all the way.";i:41;s:96:"Can happen either from the wired connector in the garage or one of the remotes from the outside.";i:42;s:72:"Sometimes its fixed by clicking again the door closes then continues to.";i:43;s:157:"If the door starts to move but stops before it reaches the floor and closes or if the door stops and then reopens something may be blocking the door sensors.";i:44;s:84:"On automatic doors the sensor lights are located on the rail usually at knee height.";i:45;s:137:"If your garage door wont open or close the problem could be a bent track a broken torsion spring or a bad capacitor int he motor housing.";i:46;s:156:"If it closes only partway the safety sensors are usually responsibleClean the lenses or realign them and make sure there are no obstacles blocking the beam.";i:47;s:127:"If the door closes while holding the button pressed you are likely having one of the following issues with your safety sensors.";i:48;s:53:"The solution is usually one or more of the following.";i:49;s:60:"The sensors are dirty - Wipe lenses with a clean soft cloth.";i:50;s:103:"They are misaligned This is the most likely problem and the most common issue with Garage Door openers.";i:51;s:30:"4- 1 wall mount and 2 remotes.";i:52;s:181:"5- The color of the learn button is orange when the door wont open the learn button goes out and when it tries to work again to open the button goes orange again and goes out again.";i:53;s:32:"6- no outages or wiring changes.";i:54;s:29:"7- we dont know what made it.";i:55;s:39:"The garage door goes down then back up.";i:56;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:57;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:58;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:59;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:60;s:34:"It may be your garage door sensor.";i:61;s:101:"There are four common problems with garage door sensors three of these homeowners can fix themselves.";i:62;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:63;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:64;s:410:"Okay now that you can open your garage door freely by hand up and down you want to make sure that the door goes down smoothly and if I get stuck a foot or two before it hits the floor then you know there is a problem with the garage door this is usually caused by rubbing on the door jamb or there is a problem with the garage door track when it gets to the bottom it does not want to close properly sometimes.";i:65;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:66;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:67;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";}}